div.div: Ganta is the only survivor after a mysterious man in red slaughters a classroom full of teenagers. He's framed for the carnage, sentenced to die, and locked away in the most twisted prison ever built: Deadman Wonderland. And then it gets worse. At Deadman Wonderland, convicts are forced into brutal deathmatches for the amusement of the masses, the cheers of the crowd drowning out the screams of the dismembered. Even when Ganta befriends Shiro, an unusual female inmate, his dark fate crushes all hope —until he discovers the strange ability to wield his spilled blood as a weapon. Ganta learns his new skill might be related to the murderous man in red and uncovers disturbing secrets that could expose those who stole his freedom. He's determined to see justice served —but first he'll have to fight for his life in a prison that holds a million ways to die. (Source: FUNimation)

While writing other people’s emotions, she may have neglected her own. Violet Evergarden, the child soldier turned Auto Memory Doll, writes letters that evoke the words her clients can’t. But when a terminally ill boy requests her services for his family, her own feelings about love and loss resurface. Now she must confront her past and the death of the Major.
(Source: Funimation)
Monster ga Afureru Sekai ni Natta kedo, Tayoreru Neko ga Iru kara Daijoubu desu.

On her way home from shopping for dinner, Kujo Ayame, a new member of society who lives with her tortoiseshell cat, Haru, gets caught up in the drastic changes in the world. The changed cityscape, monsters attacking people, and people awakening to their skills....
In the turmoil, Ayame and Haru accidentally succeed in defeating a giant monster, and at that moment, a voice echoes in their heads. ["Kujo Ayame's LV has increased from 1 to 10"]
["Confirming the first named monster defeat in Chaos Frontier Acquired the bonus skill "Search"]
With that as a trigger, Ayame made full use of her search skill to survive in a overflowing with monsters.
Moreover, Ayame is not the only one who has awakened to this skill; her cat Haru has also acquired the useful cheat-level skill "Conversion"!
(Source: GA Novels, translated)
